# Laravel Service Layer Rule

## Responsibilities

- Put business/domain logic in service classes, not controllers.
- Keep each service method focused on one use case.
- Name methods by domain intent (`createBooking`, `findBestProvider`).
- Keep return values predictable (DTO/array/resource contract).

## Service Pattern

```php
// ✅ GOOD: service orchestrates domain operations
public function createBooking(array $data): array
{
    $match = $this->matchingService->findBestProvider($data);

    return $this->persistBooking($data, $match);
}
```

## Service Quality

- Prefer constructor-injected dependencies.
- Extract reusable logic instead of duplicating across services.
- Keep database operations transactional when consistency matters.
- Throw domain-meaningful exceptions and let upper layers format responses.
